title: Will the rate of core CPI inflation be above 3.4% for the year ending in November 2024?
rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) for All Urban Consumers: All Items less Food and Energy increases by more than 3.4% in the twelve months ending November 2024 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the government shutdown.

title: Will **inflation** in 2023 be above 10.0%?
rules_primary: If the 12-month percent change in the Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items, before seasonal adjustment, according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics is above 10.0%, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
Please note that the value is not the average price level in 2023 divided by the average price level in 2022, but rather is the one decimal-value change that can be found in the December CPI report in the sentence that reads "Over the last 12 months, the all items index increased... percent before seasonal adjustment."

The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the day the earliest data is expected to be released. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or fourteen days thereafter.

rules_secondary: The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the expected release of the data. It will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or one week after the expected release of the data.

title: Will the rate of CPI inflation be above 3.4% for the year ending in December 2023?
subtitle: 3.5% or above
rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) increases by more than 3.4% in the twelve months ending December 2023 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the
government shutdown

title: Will the rate of core CPI inflation be above 4.8% for the year ending in November 2023?
subtitle: 4.9% or above
rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) for All Urban Consumers: All Items less Food and Energy increases by more than 4.8% in the twelve months ending November 2023 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the government shutdown.

title: Will the EURO/USD exchange rate be above 1.085 on April 29, 2022?
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for April 29, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is above 1.085, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  May 13, 2022. 

Please note that the data is from the Federal Reserve and represents the "noon buying rates in New York for cable transfers payable in foreign currencies". Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

title: Will the EURO/USD exchange rate be above 1.11 on April 08, 2022?
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for April 08, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is above 1.11, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  April 22, 2022. 

Please note that the data is from the Federal Reserve and represents the "noon buying rates in New York for cable transfers payable in foreign currencies". Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

title: Will the rate of core CPI inflation be above 3.3% for the year ending in February 2024?
rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) for All Urban Consumers: All Items less Food and Energy increases by more than 3.3% in the twelve months ending February 2024 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the government shutdown.

title: Will ** coreinflation** in 2025 be above_below_between ?
subtitle: 6.01 or above
rules_primary: If the 12-month percent change in the Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items less food and energy is above 6.1% or above in 2025 according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The value shall be rounded to the nearest tenth of a percent, as reported in the monthly BLS CPI news releases.

The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the earliest day the data is expected to be released. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or fourteen days thereafter.

title: What will the EURO/USD exchange rate be >1.05 on June 17, 2022?
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for June 17, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is above 1.05, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
Due to the holiday on June 20, Data is expected be released at 4:15 PM ET on June 21, 2022. The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  July 01, 2022. 

Please note that the data is from the Federal Reserve and represents the "noon buying rates in New York for cable transfers payable in foreign currencies". Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

title: Will the rate of core CPI inflation be above 3.4% for the year ending in September 2024?
rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) for All Urban Consumers: All Items less Food and Energy increases by more than 3.4% in the twelve months ending September 2024 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the government shutdown.

title: Will **inflation** in 2024 be above_below_between 6.9?
subtitle: 7.0% or above
rules_primary: If the 12-month percent change in the Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items is above 7.0 in 2024 according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
Please note that the value is rounded to the nearest tenth of a percent, as is reported in the monthly BLS CPI news releases.  Else, the market resolves to No. Please see ACPI in the Rulebook for the legally binding terms and conditions.  

The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the earliest day the data is expected to be released. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or fourteen days thereafter.

title: Will **core inflation** in 2023 be above 7.0%?
subtitle: 7.0% or higher
rules_primary: If the 12-month percent change in the Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items less food and energy is above 7.0 in 2023 according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The value shall be rounded to the nearest tenth of a percent, as reported in the monthly BLS CPI news releases. Please note that the value is not the average price level in 2023 divided by the average price level in 2022, but rather is the one decimal-value change that can be found in the December CPI report in the sentence that reads "Over the last 12 months, the all items less food and energy index increased... percent before seasonal adjustment."

The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the earliest day the data is expected to be released. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or fourteen days thereafter.

title: What will the EURO/USD exchange rate be >1.060 on June 24, 2022?
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for June 24, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is above 1.060, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
Data is expected be released at 4:15 PM ET on June 27, 2022. The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  July 08, 2022. 

Please note that the data is from the Federal Reserve and represents the "noon buying rates in New York for cable transfers payable in foreign currencies". Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

rules_secondary:
In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the
government shutdown

title: Will ** coreinflation** in 2024 be above_below_between ?
subtitle: 7.0% or higher
rules_primary: If the 12-month percent change in the Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items less food and energy is above 7.0 in 2024 according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The value shall be rounded to the nearest tenth of a percent, as reported in the monthly BLS CPI news releases.

The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the earliest day the data is expected to be released. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or fourteen days thereafter.

rules_secondary: In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the government shutdown

title: Will a replacement for **Jerome Powell** be announced by December 1, 2021?
expiration_value: The White House did not release a statement announcing a replacement for Jerome Powell. Instead, the White House released a statement saying that Biden is renominating him (available here: https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/statements-releases/2021/11/22/president-biden-nominates-jerome-powell-to-serve-as-chair-of-the-federal-reserve-dr-lael-brainard-to-serve-as-vice-chair/ )
rules_primary: If the White House releases an unretracted statement indicating that an individual other than Jerome Powell will be nominated to be the next Chair of the Federal Reserve by December 1, 2021, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: Please see FEDNOM in the Rulebook for more details.

title: Will the European Central Bank set rates above 4.74% at their meeting on Sep 12, 2024?

title: Will the EURO/USD exchange rate be above 1.09 on April 15, 2022?
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for April 15, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is above 1.09, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  April 29, 2022. 

Please note that the data is from the Federal Reserve and represents the "noon buying rates in New York for cable transfers payable in foreign currencies". Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

title: Will the EURO/USD exchange rate be between 1.08 and 1.09 on April 15, 2022?
subtitle: Between 1.08 and 1.09
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for April 15, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is between 1.08 and 1.09, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  April 29, 2022. 

Please note that the data is from the Federal Reserve and represents the "noon buying rates in New York for cable transfers payable in foreign currencies". Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

title: Will the rate of core CPI inflation be above 3.3% for the year ending in January 2025?
rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) for All Urban Consumers: All Items less Food and Energy increases by more than 3.3% in the twelve months ending January 2025 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the government shutdown.

rules_secondary: In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the government shutdown.

title: Will **inflation** in 2022 be above 8.9%?
rules_primary: If the 12-month percent change in the Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers: All Items is above 8.9% in 2022 according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
Please note that the value is not the average price level in 2022 divided by the average price level in 2021, but rather is the one decimal-value change that can be found in the December CPI report in the sentence that reads "Over the last 12 months, the all items index increased... percent before seasonal adjustment."

The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the day the earliest data is expected to be released. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or fourteen days after the expected release of the data.

The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the day the earliest data is expected to be released. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or fourteen days after the expected release of the data.

title: Will the EURO/USD exchange rate be above 1.085 on April 22, 2022?
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for April 22, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is above 1.085, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  May 06, 2022. 

Please note that the data is from the Federal Reserve and represents the "noon buying rates in New York for cable transfers payable in foreign currencies". Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) increases by more than 3.4% in the twelve months ending October 2023 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the
government shutdown

title: What will the EURO/USD exchange rate be >1.06 on May 13, 2022?
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for May 13, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is above 1.06, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  May 27, 2022. 

Please note that the data is from the Federal Reserve and represents the "noon buying rates in New York for cable transfers payable in foreign currencies". Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

title: What will the EURO/USD exchange rate be between 1.04 and 1.06 on May 13, 2022?

rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for May 13, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is between 1.04and 1.06, then the market resolves to Yes.

title: Will the rate of core PCE inflation be above 0.3% in December 2024?
subtitle: 0.4% or above
rules_primary: If the (single-decimal) month-over-month percent change in the Personal Consumption Expenditures Price Index excluding food and energy is above 0.3% in December 2024 according to the Bureau of Economic Analysis, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the expected release of the data. It will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or one week after the expected release of the data.

title: What will the EURO/USD exchange rate be >1.06 on July 01, 2022?
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for July 01, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is above 1.06, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
Due to the holiday on July 4, the data is expected be released at 4:15 PM ET on July 05, 2022. The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  July 15, 2022. 

Please note that the data is from the Federal Reserve and represents the "noon buying rates in New York for cable transfers payable in foreign currencies". Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

title: Will Emmanuel Macron leave office next in this set?
subtitle: :: President of France
rules_primary: If the Emmanuel Macron is the first leader among the above to leave office, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: An announcement that a leader will leave their position is not sufficient to resolve the Payout Criterion; the individual must actually leave and no longer hold the title. If any leader leaves solely because they have died, then all markets will resolve and the Exchange will determine the payouts to the holders of long and short positions based upon the last traded price (prior to the death) or another fair price.

title: Will the rate of CPI inflation be above 3.1% for the year ending in January 2025?
rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) increases by more than 3.1% in the twelve months ending January 2025 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the
government shutdown

title: Will the rate of core PCE inflation be above 0.3% in February 2025?
rules_primary: If the (single-decimal) month-over-month percent change in the Personal Consumption Expenditures Price Index excluding food and energy is above 0.3% in February 2025 according to the Bureau of Economic Analysis, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the expected release of the data. It will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or one week after the expected release of the data.

rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve's H.10 report reports the conversion between the U.S. dollar and the Euro for May 06, 2022 (Euro/USD) that is above 1.065, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
The market will close at 4:10 PM ET that day. The market will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of that data or  May 20, 2022.

Other exchanges may quote different values for the exchange rate with the U.S dollar. However, this market uses only the data from the Federal Reserve's H.10 release.

rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) for All Urban Consumers: All Items less Food and Energy increases by more than 3.9% in the twelve months ending October 2023 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the government shutdown.

rules_primary: If the Consumer Price Index (CPI) for All Urban Consumers: All Items less Food and Energy increases by more than 3.5% in the twelve months ending March 2025 (as represented by the one-decimal place value reported by the Bureau of Labor Statistics), then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: In the case of a delay in data caused by a federal government shutdown impacting the reliability of the Source Agency, the market’s latest Expiration Date will be extended to the sooner of the release of the Underlying or six months after the end of the government shutdown.
